<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="adequate-adj">adequate <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'ædɪkwət/    美 /'ædɪkwət/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>足够的；充分的；合乎需要的：</strong></h4>
<p>enough in quantity or good enough in quality for a particular purpose
反 inadequate </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The big house is perfectly <strong>adequate for</strong> just the two of us. 
这所大房子足够我们两个人居住。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If we hadn’t made adequate preparations, the conference wouldn’t have been so successful.
如果我们没作充分的准备，会议就不会开得那么成功。</p><footer>2012 山东</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He didn't give an adequate answer to the question.
他没有对这个问题给出满意的答复。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>adequately  /'ædɪkwətli/ adv   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I hope I will not be called on in class as I’m not yet adequately prepared. 
我希望课上不要叫到我，因为我还没准备好。</p></div></div>